page.title: 08Wildlife
page.content: The wildlife here consists of deer, rabbits, badgers, squirrels, foxes and weasels. There are also moles, and a man comes round and traps them because of the damage they do. There are only red squirrels here. There are red deer and roe deer in the forest. You often see rabbits and hares running around in the fields. You can tell the difference between a hare and a rabbit because the hare has longer ears and it is altogether larger.If you are quiet in the wood you can see bats, rats,mice and ferrets.
